Products.SupplyLimitMessage: 'Ocean Chef Usa Sea Scallops' has a supply limit of 36. The quantity in your cart has been reduced accordingly. To purchase a larger quantity, please contact us on 1800 000 610. Please note we do not supply trade orders.
Products.RichDescription:
Our juicy scallops are wild caught from the North Atlantic Ocean. Their sweet and tender flesh brings a little bit of luxury to your kitchen.

For maximum flavour caramelise in a hot pan. Pair golden brown scallops with crispy prosciutto and fresh peas for impressive elegance at home.

AdditionalAttributes.description:
Our juicy scallops are wild caught from the North Atlantic Ocean. Their sweet and tender flesh brings a little bit of luxury to your kitchen.

For maximum flavour caramelise in a hot pan. Pair golden brown scallops with crispy prosciutto and fresh peas for impressive elegance at home.
AdditionalAttributes.ingredients:
Sea Scallop, water, salt.
STORAGE:
Store below minus 18°C. Once thawed keep refrigerated below 4°C and consume within 48 hours. Do not refreeze.
THAWING:
To thaw place desired quantitu of scallops in refrigerator at below 4°C for approximately 8 hours. For quicker thawing place scallops in colander and rinse under cold water for 5 - 7 minutes, rotate scallops for even thawing.

Products.FullDescription: Ocean Chef Fish King Snapper Portions
Products.RichDescription:
Wild caught from the tropical offshore reefs of Vietnam and Indonesia. Ocean Chef King Snapper (Pristipomoides spp.) has a sweet, mild flavour and a tender bite.

Pan-fry for a crispy skin and serve with a honey, soy and chilli marinade or, if you're feeling adventurous, try Snapper pie with fennel and dill sauce.

AdditionalAttributes.description:
Wild caught from the tropical offshore reefs of Vietnam and Indonesia. Ocean Chef King Snapper (Pristipomoides spp.) has a sweet, mild flavour and a tender bite.

Pan-fry for a crispy skin and serve with a honey, soy and chilli marinade or, if you're feeling adventurous, try Snapper pie with fennel and dill sauce.
AdditionalAttributes.ingredients:
King Snapper (Pristipomoides spp)
While efforts have been made to remove bones, the occasional bone may remain.
STORAGE INSTRUCTIONS:
Store below minus 18°C. Once thawed, keep refrigerated below 4°C and consume within 48 hours. Do not refreeze.
THAWING:
To thaw place desired quantity of salmon portions in refrigeratr at below 4°C for approximately for 8 hours.

Products.RichDescription:
OCEAN CHEF PREMIUM FLATHEAD PORTIONS

The South Atlantic Ocean provides the perfect saltwater habitat for our fresh flathead. Their firm white flesh has a medium yet sweet flavour and can be baked, barbecued, poached, grilled or fried.

Flathead is most popular when battered and served with a side of chips and tangy tartare sauce. For something a bit more adventurous try pan frying in a light coating of spices served with a dollop of yogurt.

COOKING GUIDE

PAN FRY

Preheat a non-stick fry pan to a medium heat, adding 5mL olive oil, if desired. Cook thawed South American flathead fillets for 3 – 4 minutes turning occasionally. Ensure South American flathead is cooked all the way through or until piping hot in centre.

OVEN BAKE

Preheat oven to 200°C (or 180°C fan forced). Remove thawed snapper portions from packaging, place in a baking dish and cover with tinfoil. Place baking dish in oven and bake for approximately 12 – 15 minutes. Ensure snapper is cooked all the way through or until pippng hot in centre.

BBQ

Preheat BBQ to a high heat. Remove thawed portion from packaging and rub both sides with olive oil. Place snapper skin side down and cook for 3 – 4 minutes, turning only once. Ensure barramundi is cooked all the way through or until piping hot in centre.

Products.RichDescription:
OCEAN CHEF PREMIUM SMOKED HOKI PORTIONS

With a delicate smoke flavour and moist, flakey flesh, these versatile fillets can be fried, grilled, baked or barbecued. 
For best result follow tradition and poach in milk.

Serve up with chips and salad for a deliciously light meal. 

COOKING GUIDE

POACH
Poach: Place thawed smoked hoki in a saucepan. Add parsley stalks, peppercorns and garlic as desired and cover with milk. Bring to the boil then reduce to simmer for about 5 – 7 minutes. Remove fish gently from liquid and strain. Ensure smoked hoki is cooked all the way through or until piping hot in centre.

OVEN BAKE
Preheat oven to 180°C (or 200°C fan forced). Place thawed smoked hoki portions in baking dish and cover with tinfoil. Place baking dish in oven back and bake for approximately 12 – 15 minutes. Ensure smoked hoki is cooked all the way through or until piping hot in the centre.

PAN FRY
Preheat a non-stick fry pan with 5mL of olive oil to a medium heat. Cook thawed smoked hoki portions for 3 – 4 minutes turning occasionally. Ensure smoked hoki is cooked all the way through or until piping hot in the centre.
